title: Prep roundup: 3 Pacelli players headed to state
text:
Prep roundup: 3 Pacelli players headed to state Stevens Point Journal Media 11:05 p.m. CDT October 7, 2015 Assorted sports equipment on a white background (Photo: Getty Images/iStockphoto) CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
MINOCQUA – Newman Catholic sophomore Laura Larrain earned a trip to the WIAA state girls tennis tournament as she won the No. 1 singles bracket during the Division 2 sectional meet Wednesday. 
Larrain improved to 19-4 overall, and was the lone member of the Cardinals team to advance to state. 
Three Pacelli players are headed to state as well as the Cardinals finished second overall as a team. 
Cardinals sophomore Alliey Krusa won the title at No. 2 singles to qualify. Pacelli’s No. 1 doubles team of Nicole Schroeder and Tia Krzykowski also qualified for the state tournament with a second-place finish. 
Krusa won her first round over Kaitlyn Weyer of Baldwin-Woodville 6-4,4-6,6-4. In the championship round, she defeated Ruth Elmer of Amery 6-2,6-3. 
Schroeder/Krzykowski opened the day with wins over a team from Ellsworth and Emory before falling to Megan Jacobson/Hannah Zevenbergen of Baldwin-Woodville in the title match 6-1, 7-5. 
Baldwin-Woodville won the sectional title. 
Newman Catholic junior Caitlyn Chandler won the sectional title at No. 4 singles, beating Pacelli’s Stephanie Vaughan for the championship. 
Pacelli’s Julia Grygleski lost her first match at No. 1 singles and was eliminated. 
Newman Catholic’s No. 1 doubles team of Kate David and Sarah Sukanen lost their first match and were eliminated, as was Medford’s top duo of Chelsea Rausch and Shantel Faude. 
Medford’s No. 3 doubles team of Jori Brandner and Angela Taschendorf won the title at No. 3 doubles. Pacelli’s Katherine Mueller/Sophie Schroeder were third. 
Medford’s Sydney Emmerich/Ryle Anderson finished third at No. 2 doubles.

COLLEGE VOLLEYBALL 
UW-Eau Claire 3, 
UWSP 2 
STEVENS POINT – The Blugolds ended the Poitners 23-home match winning streak on UWSP’s ‘Attacking Alzheimers’ game at Berg Gym. 
Scores were 25-22, 25-22, 29-27. 
The loss was the first for UW-Stevens Point (18-5, 1-2 WIAC) at home since the Blugolds swept the Pointers in the 2013 WIAC Championship match on Nov. 3, 2012. 
Kelly Cefalu had 16 kills and 10 digs for the Pointers, her 10th straight match with at least a dozen kills, Danielle Coleman had 11 kills for UWSP. Read or Share this story: http://spjour.nl/1Lj8sD8 TOP VIDEOS
